            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>To the gods of the underworld. Kornelios Agathemeros lived 38 years.  Euphrosyne (set this up) as a memorial for her own partner in life.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
          <!--Th.K. heading; hederae; Kornelios (Cornelius) Agathemeros, erected by his wife Euphrosyne; age in years, in roman numerals, cf. . IG 14.337, 338,409, 484, 485; also, 443.1; use of idios as poss.pron. Cf. IG 14.492 (IMusCat 111) for the father or son of this man on another tombstone from the same place/monument (so Kaibel); Korhonen rather thinks it the same man erecting an inscr. in honour of his (previous) wife.-->
                </p>
            </div>
